parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Fuse Box/Fuel Pump Relay Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear fuse box and fuel pump relay can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents, especially when driving at high speeds. Additionally, the overheating of the relay can cause a fire hazard.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start
the fuel pump relay overheats
the rear fuse box melts
and there may be a burning odor or smoke.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start
there may be an electrical burning odor
and the key fob may not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start
the engine stalls
and there may be a warning light on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the park assist system can cause the driver to lose confidence in the system, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The park assist system flashes on and off intermittently and does not beep properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause a loss of brake function, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
brake fluid leaking from the brake line
rapid loss of brake fluid
complete loss of brakes
ABS light and stability control light on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the brake pedal and surrounding components can interfere with proper brake pedal operation, leading to difficulty braking and potential accidents.
symptoms: Difficulty operating the brake pedal due to limited space
inability to properly apply the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and even fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates independently without warning
the cruise control activates at random
the vehicle accelerates rapidly without driver input
the vehicle crashes into objects or other vehicles.
